==English==

===Pronunciation===
*frāz, /freɪz/, /<tt>freIz</tt>/

===Etymology===
Latin [[phrasis]] (diction) ← Greek [[φράσις]] (manner of expression), from [[φράζειν]] (to tell, to express).

====Homophones====
*[[fray]]s

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A short written or spoken expression.
# {{grammar}} A group of two or more words, such as "around the clock", that express an idea but do not form a complete sentence.
# {{music}} A small section of [[music]] in a larger piece.

====Synonyms====
*(''group of two or more words that express an idea but do not form a complete sentence''): [[expression]], [[figure of speech]], [[locution]]

